snippet: In Coach Matt Rhule’s third season, Temple has a No. 22 ranking, a victory over Penn State and a 6-0 record. He hopes an American Athletic Conference title, among other achievements, is next.
abstract: Temple, led by coach Matt Rhule, is ranked No 22 in Associated Press poll--first time team has been ranked since 1979; has chance to move to 7-0 for first time in program's history if team defeats East Carolina in upcoming game.
lead_paragraph: In Coach Matt Rhule’s third season, Temple has a No. 22 ranking, a victory over Penn State and a 6-0 record. He hopes an American Athletic Conference title, among other achievements, is next.

headline.print_headline: Temple, Unbeaten and Unlikely, Strives to Make Success Last
headline.main: A Hot Start for Temple, Where the Team Motto Is ‘What’s Next?’
